-- Veolia’s U.K. Water Business Attracts Bidders, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 2012-01-01T11:40:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/veolia-s-u-k-water-business-attracts-bidders-sunday-times-says.html
Veolia Environnement SA (VIE) ’s water
business in the U.K., which is up for sale, has drawn interest
from bidders including  Allianz SE (ALV)  and  Canada ’s Borealis pension
fund, the Sunday Times reported today, without citing anyone.  Japan ’s  Itochu Corp. (8001)  and  Marubeni Corp. (8002)  are also
considering bids, the paper said. The company plans to interview
investment banks this month to pick an adviser to run the
auction, the paper said.  The Veolia unit may be valued at as much as 1.2 billion
pounds ($1.9 billion), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nandini Sukumar in London at 
 nsukumar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
